13 §463.243. Special prestige license plate; Conserve Louisiana
14 A.(1) The secretary of the Department of Public Safety and Corrections shall
15 establish a special prestige motor vehicle license plate to be known as the "Conserve
16 Louisiana" plate, provided there is a minimum of one thousand applicants for such
17 plates. The license plates shall be restricted to use on passenger cars, pick up trucks,
18 recreational vehicles, and vans.
19 (2) The Department of Public Safety and Corrections, office of motor
20 vehicles, shall create this special prestige license plate when the applicable statutory
21 provisions are met and the department's electronic vehicle and registration system
22 is updated to accommodate the creation of the new plates.
23 B. The secretary shall work in conjunction with the Department of Wildlife
24 and Fisheries to select the color and design of the plate, provided it is in compliance
25 with R.S. 47:463(A)(3). The design shall include the words "Conserve Louisiana".
26 C. The special prestige license plate shall be issued, upon application to any
27 citizen of Louisiana in the same manner as any other motor vehicle license plate.
28 D. The fee for the plate shall be fifty dollars in addition to the standard motor
29 vehicle registration license fee, and a handling fee of three dollars and fifty cents for
30 each plate to be retained by the department to offset a portion of administrative costs.
